  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add minced garlic, red pepper flakes, and paprika; sauté for about 30 seconds.",
    "Throw in shallots and cook until translucent, around 2 minutes.",
    "Toss in shrimp, almond meal, chicken broth, lemon zest, Dijon mustard, and thyme leaves. Stir well to coat the shrimp evenly.",
    "Simmer gently for approximately 4-5 minutes until the sauce slightly thickens and the shrimp are opaque but still tender.",
    "Serve hot over steamed rice or as a side dish."
